     THE AGORAN DAILY JOURNAL
     Volume 42, Issue 1
     Wednesday, October 1, 1997

Recent events:

* The Probate system remains not-as-intended:  Rule 1738 attempts
  to limit Executors in Probate to disposing of the assets of
  deregistered Players, but Rule 1478 takes precedence and says
  that they may act generally on behalf of the deregistered
  Player.

  Morendil is thus controlling Elde, who in turn is controlling
  Blob, and the trio has had all manner of fun with the situation -
  including forming a Group called The Voodoo Lounge.  (Notary
  Murphy, who assigns Executors in Probate, has also joined the
  Group.)

* The Appeals Court is reviewing Elde's decision (actually Morendil
  acting as Elde) that Proposal 3533 (the Pragmatic Currencies reform)
  accidentally destroyed all Voting Tokens.  The debate hinges on
  whether the intermediate Game States in the middle of a Proposal's
  implementation can have side effects.

  Among the side effects of upholding the decision are four previously
  undetected Wins - two for Steve, one for Morendil, and one for
  Andre.  (You Win by Proposal if three of your Proposals in a row
  get exactly the same number of FOR/AGAINST Votes.  With no Voting
  Tokens, all 17 Proposals since Pragmatic Currencies got a 0-0 result.

  The other Rule-defined Currencies (Proposal Notes and Indulgences)
  survived because the Rules defining them take precedence over the
  Rule attempting to cause their destruction.

* Antimatter deregistered last month and is now eligible to be
  reregistered by Harlequin, eir Executor in Probate.

* Calabresi and Vanyel are Maybe Absent.  If they don't post to the
  Public Forum within two weeks, they may be deregistered for
  inactivity.

* Rule 693 (which defines a Proposal's Voting Period) has recovered
  from its Viral Infection.  It is debated whether Proposals
  submitted during the time of the Infection have their Voting
  Period begin at the time of their submission, at the time of
  the Disinfection, or whether they are completely deprived of
  a Voting Period.

* A Call For Judgement claiming that the Frankenstein Rule became
  impossible to amend (which would grant Murphy a Win by Pitchfork)
  was Judged FALSE.  However, the CFJ incorrectly specified the date
  of the supposed event, anyway.

* Proposal 3552 (Steve) - All Votes must be sent to the Public
                          Forum; Rule self-repeals after 60 days
  Proposal 3553 (Andre) - Rule 1065 (penalizing those who submit
                          too many Proposals) is repealed
  Proposal 3554 (Andre) - Players in their Grace Period are not
                          penalized for disqualifying themselves
                          from Judging a CFJ already assigned to them

* Murphy Rebels.  One more Rebel will trigger a Rebellion.

* Kolja A. creates the Currency "Koljenka".
  Oerjan creates the Currency "Euclids", with Minimum Unit
    Quantity of pi.

-- 
